EMBIRICOS v. STUYVESANT INS. CO. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. April 17, 1922.) No. 264. Certiorari denied 258 U. S.-, 43 Sup. Ct. 90, 66 L. Ed. —. Kirlin, Woolsey, Campbell, Hickox & Keating, of New York City (Delbert M. Tibbetts and Robert S. Erskine, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Prentice & Townsend, of New York City (Robert Kelly Prentice and Myron T. Townsend, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before ROGERS, MANTON, and MAYER, Circuit Judges,

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
